		<li><strong>Often repairable:</strong> Individual sections can be replaced indefinitely</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Cost Analysis: The 50% Rule</h2>

	<h3>Understanding the Cost Breakpoint</h3>
	<p>The fundamental principle for repair vs. replace decisions:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Basic rule:</strong> If repairs cost more than 50% of replacement, replace instead</li>
		<li><strong>Rationale:</strong> You're paying half the replacement cost for a fence still nearing end of life</li>
		<li><strong>Exceptions:</strong> Very new fences (under 25% of lifespan) justify higher repair ratio</li>
		<li><strong>Age adjustment:</strong> Reduce acceptable repair percentage as fence ages</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Typical Repair Costs (Stockton 2025)</h3>
	<p>Common repair scenarios and pricing:</p>

	<p><strong>Individual Board Replacement:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Pressure-treated boards:</strong> $8-15 per board installed</li>
		<li><strong>Cedar boards:</strong> $12-22 per board installed</li>
		<li><strong>Vinyl boards:</strong> $15-28 per board (if available)</li>
		<li><strong>Quantity impact:</strong> Under 10 boards, higher per-unit cost</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Post Replacement:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Single post (4x4):</strong> $85-150 including concrete</li>
		<li><strong>Corner/gate post (6x6):</strong> $120-200 including concrete</li>
		<li><strong>Metal post:</strong> $75-140 depending on type</li>
		<li><strong>Labor component:</strong> 60-70% of cost due to excavation work</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Panel Section Replacement:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>8-foot wood panel section:</strong> $180-320 installed</li>
		<li><strong>8-foot vinyl panel section:</strong> $220-380 installed</li>
		<li><strong>Includes:</strong> Posts (if needed), rails, boards, hardware</li>
		<li><strong>Efficiency:</strong> Cost per section decreases with multiple sections</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Gate Repairs:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Hinge replacement:</strong> $45-85 per gate</li>
		<li><strong>Latch replacement:</strong> $35-75</li>
		<li><strong>Gate rebuild (sagging fix):</strong> $120-250</li>
		<li><strong>Complete gate replacement:</strong> $250-700 depending on size/material</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Structural Reinforcement:</strong></p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Post bracing:</strong> $60-120 per post</li>
		<li><strong>Additional rail installation:</strong> $85-150 per 8-foot section</li>
		<li><strong>Wind damage repair:</strong> $300-800 depending on extent</li>
	</ul>

